results.name: Number of unlabeled set-systems covering n vertices with no endpoints.
comment: A set-system is a finite set of finite nonempty sets. An endpoint is a vertex appearing only once (degree 1).
example: Non-isomorphic representatives of the a(3) = 20 set-systems:
xref: First differences of the non-covering version A330124.
Unlabeled set-systems with no endpoints counted by vertices are A317794.
Unlabeled set-systems with no endpoints counted by weight are A330054.
Unlabeled set-systems counted by vertices are A000612.
Unlabeled set-systems counted by weight are A283877.
